The paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are topics typically covered in the computer science subcategories of game theory (cs.GT) and economics and computation (cs.EC). The use of valuation functions and the analysis of their properties suggest a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The examination of strategies for ensuring individual rationality and the use of secure bidding suggest a connection to cryptography (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
